NBA legend Kobe Bryant died on Sunday in a helicopter crash in suburban Los Angeles, celebrity website TMZ reported, saying five people are confirmed dead in the incident. He was 41. A helicopter crash in the hills near Calabasas was also confirmed by the Los Angeles Times. The incident came only hours after the former Los Angeles Lakers star, 41, was passed by current Lakers star LeBron James for third on the all-time NBA scoring list in a Saturday game at Philadelphia. According to TMZ, the former Los Angeles Lakers basketball player was traveling with four other people in his private helicopter when it crashed, killing everyone on board. Kobe is widely considered one of the greatest NBA players of all time. He has won 5 NBA championships, 2 NBA Finals MVPs during his 20 years at the Lakers. Bryant is survived by his wife Vanessa and their four daughters - Gianna, Natalia and Bianca and newborn Capri. This is a developing story  https://www.sport24.co.za/OtherSport/International/nba-great-kobe-bryant-killed-in-helicopter-crash-20200126